			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>The Resumator is a quirky, Pittsburgh-based software company that is reinventing the way employers hire. </strong>We empower growing businesses with recruiting tools they&#39;ve never had, but have always needed. Our customers include some of the fastest growing businesses and hottest startups across the world. The Resumator offers competitive salaries and full benefits, including health, dental, vision, disability, life insurance, PTO, your birthday off, days to volunteer and stock options. Perks include free parking, relaxed dress code, MacBook computers, Wii and Xbox gaming systems and work from home days. We&#39;re one of Pittsburgh&rsquo;s hottest companies and we&rsquo;re growing fast. Come join the team!</p>
<p>
<strong>We&rsquo;re looking for a tenacious Marketing leader who has proven track record of generating large volumes of high-quality B2B leads through online marketing.</strong> We have an audience of over 500,000 businesses that could use The Resumator. Can you help us cost-effectively target this audience and generate interest in our service?</p>
<p>
<strong>DIRECTOR OF MARKETING</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Conceive, develop and oversee the execution and success of all marketing-related programs, including&nbsp;press releases, emails, direct mail, website content, social media updates and blog posts, conference and tradeshow materials, white papers, product sheets, merchandising, brochures and other sales and marketing collateral.</li>
<li>
Manage the oversight of all aspects of search engine marketing, retargeting and affiliate programs, including the tracking and ongoing improvement of KPIs.</li>
<li>
Oversee the ongoing management of content and design of The Resumator website, including the development of landing pages, partners pages, blog content and the optimization of key conversion funnel pages.</li>
<li>
Support press release strategy by developing content for press releases with management team.</li>
<li>
Manage brand messaging for external activities such as conference presence and advertising.</li>
<li>
Act as the company contact for all media inquiries and public relations to ensure a uniform, consistent product and corporate image though the media.</li>
<li>
Work closely with sales, product management and development groups to coordinate all marketing communication efforts and produce sales tools, product sheets etc.</li>
<li>
Ensure all marketing efforts have appropriate metrics tracked for easy reporting.</li>
<li>
Develop channel specific marketing budget and manage all expenses while ensuring programs stay on budget.</li>
<li>
Make strong recommendations for recruiting marketing employees and interns.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A least three years of experience as a B2B marketing executive in a technology company.</li>
<li>
Willingness and ability to convey your communications POV when working with and for senior level executives.</li>
<li>
Ability to complete multiple tasks and high volume of work on short deadlines and follow through on assigned tasks with limited supervision.</li>
<li>
Strong knowledge of how to track website conversion rates, visitor traffic and other metrics.</li>
<li>
Experience not just leading a team, but executing actual marketing tasks as well.</li>
<li>
Strong leadership skills that are readily perceived.</li>
<li>
Risk-taking attitude but expects accountability.</li>
<li>
Experience driving website traffic using inbound marketing tactics.</li>
<li>
Proven, measurable track record of success.</li>
<li>
Confidence you can deliver results even with a limited budget.</li>
<li>
Working knowledge of Adobe Suite of products.</li>
<li>
Excellent writing skills.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus Points</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience marketing SaaS offering a HUGE plus.</li>
<li>
Experience working at a venture-backed startup a plus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>NO RECRUITERS PLEASE!</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Included in Entrepreneur magazine&rsquo;s list of &ldquo;100 Brilliant Companies,&rdquo; The Resumator has been widely heralded as an innovative, essential product for businesses that need to hire. </strong>The Resumator has been called a &ldquo;life-changing&rdquo; service and &ldquo;one of the best SaaS tools I&rsquo;ve ever used.&rdquo; Our software interface is beautiful. Our customer demos are a love-fest. We&rsquo;re building a great company where people want to come to work, and we&rsquo;re looking for creative, tenacious people to join our team.</p>
<p>
<strong>Most importantly, we are an entrepreneurial-focused company. </strong>We want all of our folks to learn what it takes to start their own business someday, which means much of our company information is transparent. This is an excellent opportunity to gain skills to someday manage your own online business.</p>
